The Color Science of Skin

![PANTONE SkinTone Guide](https://www.pantone.com/media/wysiwyg/pages/skintone/pantone-skintone-the-color-science-of-skin.jpg?auto=webp&format=pjpg&quality=85)

Pantone® color scientists deliberately and diligently sought out an inclusive and wide variety of skin tone samples from volunteers around the world in order to update the new SkinTone™ Guide to be representative of the full spectrum of human skin types.

Scientific measurements were taken from different body parts with the use of a handheld X-Rite spectrophotometer, a precise color measuring instrument capable of separating out surface and appearance effects to measure only the color of an object.

That measurement data was then spectrally matched using paint on paper to produce scientifically accurate swatches on the richly pigmented SkinTone™ Guide.

![Pantone SkinTone Guide](https://www.pantone.com/media/wysiwyg/pantone-fhi-beauty-bundle-lifestyle-2-updated-landing-page.jpg?auto=webp&format=pjpg&quality=85)

Unlock Your Beauty Creativity with Pantone's® Beauty Bundle

The Pantone® Beauty Bundle is a great option for Cosmetic and Beauty Product Developers who want to take their creativity to the next level. It includes four products that provide access to over 2,800 Pantone Colors for Fashion, Home + Interiors, as well as 138 spectrally matched skin tones.

